title: Can't See Match History on LoL Website?
body: I haven't been able to see my own match history's on the LoL website for almost a week now so I thought it was something with my account but I can't see any match histories, including the ones from pro games. Is this a problem for everyone or is it just me, and how do I fix it?

replies.body:
I looked up your match history and everything looks okay to me!  Try resetting your [cache and cookies](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies) to make sure nothing is preventing your browser from loading it.  Make sure you're going to the correct link as well:

http://matchhistory.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-history/NA1/233448961

I hope that helps!

Didn't work but in the other comment someone sent me a link to an extension someone created to fix it. That browser extension works, is that from Riot or did someone else make it? I just pressed the extension icon and boom all my match history showed up.

I have his same problem about my match history, trying to access it directly from my zone (euw) site gives the general match history blank page: http://matchhistory.euw.leagueoflegends.com/en/

while going on euw boards profile and the go to my match history gives: http://matchhistory.euw.leagueoflegends.com/en/#match-history/EUW1/42013767 which still displays as the blank match history page.

I tried clenaing my cache and cookies but it didn't solve the problem.
